    <li
    
    
    ><div class="comment" id="c34870">
        
    <p>Regarding iNames, you can still render them as links. Just use the XRI resolution format: <a href="http://xri.net/=whatever" rel="nofollow">http://xri.net/=whatever</a>. I logged in w/ my OpenID, but my iName is =trei and so the url is <a href="http://xri.net/=trei" rel="nofollow">http://xri.net/=trei</a>. More info about all that at <a href="http://xri.net" rel="nofollow">http://xri.net</a>.</p>
    <p class="commentFooter">
      
        <a href="http://trei.myopenid.com" rel="nofollow">Trei Brundrett</a>
       - 20th December 2006 03:24 - <a href="/2006/Dec/19/openid/#c34870" title="Permalink for comment 31">#</a></p>
