    <li
    
    class="openid"
    
    ><div class="comment" id="c34965">
        
    Ok, I think I figure out the issue. In the delegate, you must put the full http protocol around your delegate name. However, when you sign in with OpenID (at least on the sites I tried), you do not need to put the http around the delegate name.

To be safe, you can just put http around everything, even when you sign in.
    <p class="commentFooter">
      
      <strong><img alt="" src="/static/css/img/openid-14x14.png" style="vertical-align: top; padding-top: 3px"> <a href="http://alchemista.dealraider.com/" rel="nofollow">Steve</a></strong>
       - 23rd December 2006 14:28 - <a href="/2006/Dec/19/openid/#c34965" title="Permalink for comment 74">#</a></p>
