    <p>I tried signing in on your site here using my homepage address, but it didn't work, I kept getting a 404 not found error. I can sign in using my TypeKey profile URI, though. Additionally, I tried to log in using again, my homepage URI at <a href="http://www.openidenabled.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.openidenabled.com/</a> and was able to hop on and authenticate through TypeKey without a hitch. For any readers of yours looking for how to do this with TypeKey (I couldn't find the info on the TypeKey site) is this:<br />&lt;code&gt;[link rel="openid.delegate" href="http://profile.typekey.com/username/" /] [link rel="openid.server" href="https://www.typekey.com/t/openid" /]&lt;/code&gt;<br />Just replace every "[ ]" set with "&lt; &gt;"<br />Good luck to all, hope to see this spread.</p>
    <p class="commentFooter">
      
      <strong><img alt="" src="/static/css/img/openid-14x14.png" style="vertical-align: top; padding-top: 3px"> <a href="http://profile.typekey.com/typekeybriandigitalcom/" rel="nofollow">Brian</a></strong>
